body_raw:
Let $\mu$ and $
u$ be nonnegative Borel measures on $[0,+\infty)$ and let measure $\mu$ be finite, i.e. $\mu \{ [0,+\infty) \} < \infty$. For any $p > 0$ the equality holds $$    \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} e^{-px} \mu(dx) = \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} e^{-px} 
u(dx). $$ Passing to the limit $p 	o +0$ and using Lebesgue dominated convergence theorem we receive $$    \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} \mu(dx) = \lim\limits_{p 	o +0} \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} e^{-px} 
u(dx) < \infty. $$ Is it true that measure $
u$ is finite in general? If I'm not mistaken we can use monotone convergence theorem to pass to the limit under the integral sign. More precisely, $e^{-p_n x}$ is a monotone nondecreasing sequence of functions if $p_n$ is a decreasing sequence with zero limit. Furthermore, $e^{-p_n x} 	o 1$. Then $1$ is $
u$-integrable and $$    \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} \mu(dx) = \lim\limits_{p 	o +0} \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} e^{-px} 
u(dx) = \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} \lim\limits_{p 	o +0} e^{-px} 
u(dx) = \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} 
u(dx) $$

body_text:
Let $\mu$ and $
u$ be nonnegative Borel measures on $[0,+\infty)$ and let measure $\mu$ be finite, i.e. $\mu \{ [0,+\infty) \} < \infty$. For any $p > 0$ the equality holds $$    \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} e^{-px} \mu(dx) = \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} e^{-px} 
u(dx). $$ Passing to the limit $p 	o +0$ and using Lebesgue dominated convergence theorem we receive $$    \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} \mu(dx) = \lim\limits_{p 	o +0} \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} e^{-px} 
u(dx) < \infty. $$ Is it true that measure $
u$ is finite in general? If I'm not mistaken we can use monotone convergence theorem to pass to the limit under the integral sign. More precisely, $e^{-p_n x}$ is a monotone nondecreasing sequence of functions if $p_n$ is a decreasing sequence with zero limit. Furthermore, $e^{-p_n x} 	o 1$. Then $1$ is $
u$-integrable and $$    \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} \mu(dx) = \lim\limits_{p 	o +0} \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} e^{-px} 
u(dx) = \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} \lim\limits_{p 	o +0} e^{-px} 
u(dx) = \int\limits_{0}^{\infty} 
u(dx) $$

